  "body": "<!-- Briefly describe the issue you're experiencing. Tell us what you were trying to do and what happened instead. -->\r\n\r\nDue to the use of `abi.decode`, [which reverts on failure,](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/5902#issuecomment-458868819)  in SafeERC-20, successful Uniswap `transfer`s (which have a standard return value of true, but of non-standard size, apparently, perhaps a vyper bug) are reverted. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/9e19d90cd9df3897e499753aa7951c0bc7759df7/contracts/token/ERC20/SafeERC20.sol#L72\r\n\r\nThis prevents Aragon orgs, for example, from allowing users to withdraw these tokens, [as I've bumped into here ðŸ˜…](https://github.com/aragon/aragon-apps/issues/1028) \r\n\r\nEdit: this may just be a documentation issue - the previous description of `must equal true` is more accurate than the current description of `not false`. The most accurate description would be `must be a single truthy value` ðŸ˜…. \r\n<!-- Remember, this is not a place to ask for help debugging code. For that, we welcome you in the OpenZeppelin Community Forum: https://forum.openzeppelin.com/. -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tell us what version of OpenZeppelin Contracts you're using, and how you're using it: Truffle, Remix, etc. -->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the problem you have been experiencing in more detail. Include as much information as you think is relevant. Keep in mind that transactions can fail for many reasons; context is key here. -->\r\n\r\n<!-- We will be able to better help if you provide a minimal example that triggers the bug. -->\r\n",
